# Write Architectural Decision — Procedure

**Single source of truth:** `docs/mimari-kararlar.md` — there is **no** `docs/adr/` folder in this project. Rules and code reference karar IDs like `[TS-012]`, `[AUTH-004]`; they do not duplicate full decision text.

## Step 0: When an ADR Is Required

Record a decision **before** implementation when:

| Trigger | Example |
| --- | --- |
| New framework or major library | Redis client swap, ORM change |
| Stack pin change | React state library, test runner |
| Unresolved Bölüm 18 open item | `[INF-OPEN-1]` deployment platform |
| Cross-cutting security/auth change | Token storage model change |
| Pattern not covered by existing karar | New real-time transport |

**Not required:** routine CRUD, bug fixes, following existing pinned stack (`00-project-identity.mdc`).

Load: `docs/mimari-kararlar.md` (full index + Bölüm 18), related `docs/0x` spec.

## Step 1: Check Existing Kararlar

Search `docs/mimari-kararlar.md` for related IDs:

```bash
rg "AUTH-|TS-|INF-|CODE-" docs/mimari-kararlar.md
```

| Outcome | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Karar exists and fits | Reference ID in PR; **no new entry** |
| Karar exists but wrong | Supersede with new ID + note old ID deprecated |
| Open item matches | Close `[KATEGORI-OPEN-N]` in Bölüm 18 |
| No coverage | Add new karar (Step 2) |

## Step 2: Choose Karar ID Format

Format: `[KATEGORI-SIRA]` or `[KATEGORI-OPEN-N]` for open items.

| Prefix | Domain |
| --- | --- |
| `P-` | Project scope, MVP |
| `TS-` | Tech stack |
| `INF-` | Infrastructure |
| `AUTH-` / `SEC-` | Security, authorization |
| `CODE-` | Coding conventions |
| `R-` | Roles |
| `AP-` | Admin panel |

Next sequence: scan section for highest number, increment.

Open decisions → Bölüm 18 with priority: 🔴 high, 🟠 medium, 🟢 low.

## Step 3: Write Karar Entry

Add under the **correct section** (1–17), not a separate file:

```markdown
**Karar [TS-0XX]:** <Short title> — <Chosen option>. <1–3 sentence rationale>.
Gerekçe: <why this over alternatives>. İlgili: `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm X.
```

Required elements:

```
[ ] Karar ID unique
[ ] Decision stated imperatively (what we do)
[ ] Rationale (why — scale, security, MVP scope)
[ ] Rejected alternatives mentioned briefly if non-obvious
[ ] Links to affected docs sections
[ ] MVP in/out explicit if scope decision
```

Example style (from existing doc):

> **Karar [AUTH-002]:** Yetki çözümleme stratejisi — **Runtime, cache'siz**. ...

## Step 4: Update Bölüm 18 (Open Decisions)

If closing an open item:

1. Remove row from Bölüm 18 table/list.
2. Add resolved karar in proper section.
3. Note in version footer (bottom of doc): date + ID closed.

If **cannot** decide (deployment platform unset):

- Do **not** implement dependent code.
- Leave `[INF-OPEN-N]` open.
- Code: `// TODO: [INF-OPEN-1] — mimari karar gerekiyor`

Agent must not assume open decisions ([CODE-004]).

## Step 5: Propagate to Spec Docs

Update affected specs in **same PR** as karar:

| Karar type | Update |
| --- | --- |
| API contract | `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` |
| DB | `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` |
| Backend module | `docs/04_BACKEND_SPEC.md` |
| Frontend | `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` |
| Security | `docs/07_SECURITY_IMPLEMENTATION.md` |
| Roadmap impact | `docs/10_IMPLEMENTATION_ROADMAP.md` |

`.mdc` rules get **ID reference only** — not full karar text. Update `00-project-identity.mdc` only if stack pin table changes (rare; human review).

## Step 6: Do NOT Create docs/adr/

This project consolidates decisions in `mimari-kararlar.md` per project convention. No MADR files under `docs/adr/`.

## Step 7: PR and Commit

```
docs(mimari): add [TS-0XX] decision for <topic>
```

PR sections:

```markdown
## Karar
[TS-0XX]: <title>

## Etkilenen spec
- docs/04 Bölüm X
- docs/03 Bölüm Y

## Implementation follow-up
- [ ] Feature PR after merge
```

Decisions merge **before** or **with** implementation PR — never silent divergence.

## Step 8: Reference in Code and Rules

In code comments (sparingly):

```typescript
// Campaign list filtered by membership — [AUTH-004]
```

In PR description: `Implements [TS-0XX]`.

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Creating `docs/adr/0001-*.md` parallel track
- ❌ Implementing before karar for stack/open items
- ❌ Copying entire Bölüm 14 stack table into `.mdc`
- ❌ Karar without rationale
- ❌ Leaving Bölüm 18 open item while coding dependent feature
- ❌ Superseding karar without documenting old ID deprecated

