Place new karar in the section that owns the concern — not a catch-all appendix.

## Superseding a Karar

When reversing a decision:

```markdown
**Karar [TS-0XX]:** … (supersedes [TS-00Y], deprecated 2026-06-17)
```

Keep old ID in doc with strikethrough note — do not delete history without human approval. Update `00-project-identity.mdc` stack table only when pin changes.

## Relationship to phase-creator

Phase rules reference karar IDs; phase-creator does not duplicate karar text. New faz scope requiring new stack → ADR **before** phase `.mdc` approval.

## Examples Requiring Karar

| Request | Why |
| --- | --- |
| Switch Zustand for Redux | Stack pin change [TS-*] |
| Add GraphQL alongside REST | API strategy |
| Store access token in cookie | Security [SEC-*] |
| Add MongoDB for logs | Infrastructure |

## Examples NOT Requiring Karar

| Request | Why |
| --- | --- |
| Add campaign PATCH field | Spec in docs/03 |
| Extract CampaignPolicy | Pattern already [AUTH-003] |
| Fix 404 test | Bug fix |

## Troubleshooting

| Mistake | Fix |
| --- | --- |
| Implemented before karar | Revert or pause; write karar; re-implement |
| Duplicate ID | Search doc; use next free sequence |
| Karar in PR only | Must land in mimari-kararlar.md same merge |

## Checklist

```
[ ] Searched existing kararlar — no duplicate
[ ] ID format [KATEGORI-NNN] correct
[ ] Entry in correct section of mimari-kararlar.md
[ ] Bölüm 18 updated if resolving open item
[ ] Related docs/0x sections updated
[ ] No docs/adr/ file created
[ ] Implementation blocked until merged (if open decision was blocker)
```

